This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel regularization approach to train neural networks that improves generalization and test error. The paper also evaluates the proposed algorithm on several neural network architectures and datasets. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as neural networks are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as neural networks are a fundamental component of AI. 

It may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper focuses on training neural networks. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as neural networks are used in various applications related to social and information networks.
